				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The "ticking time bomb" scenario is an interesting diversion, nothing more, because there is no "ticking time bomb" scenario. We don't know if any detainee at Gitmo or elsewhere has any information on any future terrorist attack. How many innocent people can be tortured for the POSSIBILITY there's a ticking time bomb?
<br />

<br />
And the line between valid interrogation techniques and torture is only a fine one if you accept the presupposition that any interrogation technique short of torture is valid. I don't. There should be quite a gulf between where valid interrogation ends and torture begins.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
