				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">But if I slapped the shit out of Jeff Dahmer and he subsequently 'fessed up to his murders, I would be severely dissapointed in our justice system letting him off the hook. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Jesus H. Christ, man. That's EXACTLY when an accused murderer should be sprung. No confession gotten through torture should be considered valid, or reliable. If I rubber hosed you for 24 hours, you'd sign a confession to Jeff Dahmer's murders too!
<br />

<br />
I'd MUCH rather err on the side of liberty than to let overzealous cops with a martyr impulse sacrifice their careers to make sure someone THEY ARE DAMN SURE IS GUILTY goes to prison by forcing a confession through torture.
<br />

<br />
If you want to make the argument that vital information (say, the location of a kidnapped child) gained through torture shouldn't be ignored, that's a murkier argument. But the one you present has absolutely no gray area, and you are dead wrong.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Certainly I do not advocate violent interrogation or physical abuse. There are other means. Unfortunately in the care bear world we are trying to create, even putting a prisoner in a mentally fatiguing situation is called torture.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Depends. Questioning a prisoner for 16 hours straight? Not a problem. Putting them in a room where loud music is playing and bright lights are shining and sleep is impossible for four days straight? That's torture. 
<br />

<br />
Even dripping water has been called torture in the past. "Chinese water torture" anyone? Why change the rules now?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
