				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">That's a very muddy ethical situation, I agree. And again, what you're talking about has been given the sobriquet of "the ticking time-bomb scenario." It's a very common argument. It's considered specious by many because it represents an extremely, extremely small percentage of torture cases, and as far as anybody knows, NONE of the torture cases alleged to have been perpetrated by the US, its agents, or its allies via deportation from the US.
<br />

<br />
Which makes it, for these purposes, moot.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
